nship between the individual and the state and, in turn, contribute to a new and richer understanding of the role of the citizen in modern democracies.This updated edition features a new preface by the author, in which she articulates how, over the past decade, dignity rights cases have evolved to incorporate the convergence of human rights and environmental rights that we have seen at the international level and in domestic constitutions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 0aDignity. 0aRespect for personsxLaw and legislation. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Human Rights.2bisacsh  aHuman Rights.  aLaw.  aPolitical Science.  aPublic Policy.1 aBarak, Aharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaly, Erin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073921340uhttps://doi.org/10.9783/9780812224795?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780812224795423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780812224795/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070472-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073921-3  University of Pennsylvania Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPA